---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Penetration Testing Services | Texas Cybersecurity | Sheepdog Cyber Defense" description="Veteran-owned penetration testing and red teaming services in San Antonio, Bulverde, Spring Branch. External, internal, web app, and physical security testing." showMatrix={true}>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-logo-container">
      <img src="https://assets.esecurityplanet.com/uploads/2024/10/esp_20241008-chinese-hackers-breach-wiretapping-data.png" alt="Hacker" class="hacker-bg">
      <img src="/images/logo.svg" alt="Sheepdog Cyber Defense" class="hero-logo">
    </div>
    <h1>Security Testing Done Right</h1>
    <p class="lead">We help Texas businesses find weaknesses before the bad guys do. Plainspoken advice. Thorough testing. No jargon.</p>
    <div class="cta-group">
      <a href="/contact" class="btn">Get in Touch</a>
      <a href="/services" class="btn-secondary">Our Services</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="trust-signals">
    <div class="signal">
      <span class="label">Veteran Owned</span>
      <span class="detail">Founded by military veterans</span>
    </div>
    <div class="signal">
      <span class="label">Since 2022</span>
      <span class="detail">Serving Texas businesses</span>
    </div>
    <div class="signal">
      <span class="label">Certifications</span>
      <span class="detail">CRTO, PNPT, GWAPT, eCPPTv2, PWPA, CEH</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="service-areas">
    <h2>Serving Bulverde, Spring Branch, San Antonio & Surrounding Areas</h2>
    <p>We work with businesses throughout the Texas Hill Country and Greater San Antonio region.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="services-preview">
    <h2>Our Services</h2>
    <div class="service-grid">
      <a href="/services/external-penetration-testing" class="service-card">
        <h3>External Penetration Testing</h3>
        <p>Test your external-facing systems from an attacker's perspective.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/services/internal-penetration-testing" class="service-card">
        <h3>Internal Penetration Testing</h3>
        <p>Assess what happens after an attacker gains network access.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/services/web-application-penetration-testing" class="service-card">
        <h3>Web Application Testing</h3>
        <p>Find vulnerabilities in your web applications and APIs.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/services/red-teaming" class="service-card">
        <h3>Red Teaming</h3>
        <p>Realistic attack scenarios to test your team's detection and response.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/services/physical-site-review" class="service-card">
        <h3>Physical Site Review</h3>
        <p>Assess physical security controls and facility vulnerabilities.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
    <p><a href="/services">View all services &rarr;</a></p>
  </section>

  <section class="why-choose">
    <h2>Why Choose Sheepdog Cyber Defense</h2>
    <div class="features-grid">
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Expert Certifications</h3>
        <p>Our team holds industry-leading credentials: CRTO, PNPT, GWAPT, eCPPTv2, PWPA, and CEH. We stay current with evolving threat landscapes and attack methodologies.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Real-World Experience</h3>
        <p>Founded by military veterans, we bring combat-tested security expertise to every engagement. We understand both offensive and defensive perspectives.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Plain Language Advice</h3>
        <p>No jargon. No overwhelming reports. We explain findings clearly so your team understands the risks and how to fix them—without technical double-talk.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Texas-Based Support</h3>
        <p>Serving Bulverde, Spring Branch, San Antonio, and the Texas Hill Country since 2022. Local presence with accessible consultants you can meet face-to-face.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="compliance-standards">
    <h2>Security Testing for Compliance & Standards</h2>
    <p>Penetration testing is essential for meeting industry compliance requirements and demonstrating security maturity to stakeholders and partners.</p>
    <div class="standards-list">
      <div class="standard">
        <h4>PCI-DSS</h4>
        <p>Payment Card Industry security requires regular penetration testing to validate payment processing security.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="standard">
        <h4>HIPAA</h4>
        <p>Healthcare organizations must assess security controls regularly. Our testing helps meet HIPAA Security Rule requirements.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="standard">
        <h4>SOC 2</h4>
        <p>Service organizations demonstrate security controls to clients through SOC 2 audits, where penetration testing validates trust.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="standard">
        <h4>NIST Cybersecurity Framework</h4>
        <p>Federal contractors and government agencies rely on penetration testing as part of NIST compliance and risk assessment.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="standard">
        <h4>ISO 27001</h4>
        <p>International information security standards benefit from regular penetration testing to identify control gaps.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="standard">
        <h4>Texas-Specific Requirements</h4>
        <p>State and local regulations may require security assessments. We help Texas businesses stay compliant with state-level data protection laws.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p><a href="/faq#compliance">Learn more about compliance testing in our FAQ &rarr;</a></p>
  </section>

  <section class="testing-frequency">
    <h2>How Often Should You Do Penetration Testing?</h2>
    <p>The answer depends on your business, industry, and risk profile. Most organizations benefit from annual testing, but some need more frequent assessments.</p>
    <div class="frequency-options">
      <div class="option">
        <h4>Annual Testing</h4>
        <p>Standard practice for most organizations. Identifies new vulnerabilities as your systems and threats evolve.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="option">
        <h4>After Major Changes</h4>
        <p>New applications, infrastructure changes, or security patches warrant retesting to ensure changes didn't introduce vulnerabilities.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="option">
        <h4>Quarterly or Continuous</h4>
        <p>High-risk industries and organizations handling sensitive data often benefit from more frequent testing or continuous monitoring.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p><a href="/blog/how-often-should-you-pentest">Read our detailed guide on penetration testing frequency &rarr;</a></p>
  </section>

  <section class="testimonials-preview">
    <h2>What Our Clients Say</h2>
    <div class="testimonials-grid">
      <div class="testimonial-card">
        <p>"We were planning to do penetration testing 'someday' but didn't know where to start. Sheepdog made the process straightforward and the report was actually understandable. Our team felt confident implementing their recommendations."</p>
        <p class="attribution">— IT Director, San Antonio Tech Company</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="testimonial-card">
        <p>"The findings weren't just a list of vulnerabilities with technical jargon. They explained what each issue meant for our business and gave us clear steps to fix them. Worth every penny."</p>
        <p class="attribution">— Operations Manager, Spring Branch Manufacturing</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="testimonial-card">
        <p>"Red teaming felt intimidating at first, but it was the validation we needed to show our board that our security investments were working. The team was professional and the debrief was incredibly valuable."</p>
        <p class="attribution">— CISO, San Antonio Financial Services</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 2rem;"><a href="/testimonials">Read more client stories and case studies &rarr;</a></p>
  </section>

  <section class="blog-preview">
    <h2>Learn More From Our Blog</h2>
    <p>Understand penetration testing costs, frequency, and strategies for your business:</p>
    <div class="blog-links">
      <a href="/blog/penetration-testing-costs-roi" class="blog-card">
        <h4>Penetration Testing Costs & ROI</h4>
        <p>Understand pricing, budget considerations, and why the ROI far exceeds the cost of testing.</p>
      </a>
      
      <a href="/blog/red-teaming-vs-pentesting" class="blog-card">
        <h4>Red Teaming vs Penetration Testing</h4>
        <p>Complete guide comparing these two approaches and determining which is right for you.</p>
      </a>
      
      <a href="/blog/how-often-should-you-pentest" class="blog-card">
        <h4>How Often Should You Test?</h4>
        <p>Comprehensive guide to testing frequency based on your industry, risk profile, and compliance requirements.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <h2>Ready to Test Your Security?</h2>
    <p>Drop us a line and we'll get back to you within 24 hours or next business day.</p>
    <a href="/contact" class="btn">Contact Us</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }
  
  .hero-logo-container {
    perspective: 1000px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    position: relative;
    animation: screenShake 0.6s ease-out 2.8s;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  
  @keyframes screenShake {
    0%, 100% { transform: translateX(0) translateY(0) rotate(0); }
    10% { transform: translateX(-20px) translateY(-5px) rotate(-1deg); }
    20% { transform: translateX(15px) translateY(5px) rotate(1deg); }
    30% { transform: translateX(-12px) translateY(-3px); }
    40% { transform: translateX(10px) translateY(2px); }
    50% { transform: translateX(-6px); }
    60% { transform: translateX(4px); }
    70% { transform: translateX(-2px); }
  }
  
  .hacker-bg {
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    width: 1120px;
    height: auto;
    opacity: 0.7;
    z-index: -1;
    border-radius: 10px;
    animation: fadeOut 0.5s ease-out 2.5s forwards;
  }
  
  @keyframes fadeOut {
    to {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translate(-50%, -50%) scale(1.2);
    }
  }
  
  @keyframes screenShake {
    0%, 100% { transform: translateX(0) rotate(0); }
    10% { transform: translateX(-15px) rotate(-2deg); }
    20% { transform: translateX(12px) rotate(1.5deg); }
    30% { transform: translateX(-10px) rotate(-1deg); }
    40% { transform: translateX(8px) rotate(0.5deg); }
    50% { transform: translateX(-5px); }
    60% { transform: translateX(3px); }
  }
  
  .hero-logo-container::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    background: var(--accent);
    border-radius: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    animation: impactRing 1.8s ease-out 1.8s forwards;
    opacity: 0;
    box-shadow: 0 0 150px 75px var(--accent);
  }
  
  @keyframes impactRing {
    0% {
      width: 10px;
      height: 10px;
      opacity: 1;
      box-shadow: 0 0 200px 100px var(--accent);
    }
    20% {
      opacity: 1;
      box-shadow: 0 0 300px 150px var(--accent);
    }
    100% {
      width: 1800px;
      height: 1800px;
      opacity: 0;
    }
  }
  
  .hero-logo {
    height: 560px;
    width: auto;
    animation: logoSlam 1.8s cubic-bezier(0.17, 0.67, 0.12, 1.5) 1s forwards;
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateX(-200vw) rotate(-45deg) scale(0.5);
    filter: brightness(2) blur(10px);
    z-index: 2;
    position: relative;
  }
  
  @keyframes logoSlam {
    0% {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateX(-200vw) rotate(-45deg) scale(0.5);
      filter: brightness(4) blur(20px);
    }
    10% {
      opacity: 1;
    }
    50% {
      transform: translateX(50px) rotate(10deg) scale(1.3);
      filter: brightness(3) blur(8px);
    }
    70% {
      transform: translateX(-20px) rotate(-3deg) scale(0.85);
      filter: brightness(1.5) blur(2px);
    }
    85% {
      transform: translateX(10px) rotate(1deg) scale(1.05);
      filter: brightness(1.1) blur(0px);
    }
    95% {
      transform: translateX(-5px) scale(0.98);
    }
    100% {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateX(0) rotate(0deg) scale(1);
      filter: brightness(1) blur(0px);
    }
  }
  
  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    animation: fadeInUp 0.6s ease-out 3.2s backwards;
  }
  
  @keyframes fadeInUp {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(20px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }
  
  .lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
    animation: fadeInUp 0.6s ease-out 3.4s backwards;
  }
  
  .cta-group {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    animation: fadeInUp 0.6s ease-out 3.6s backwards;
  }
  
  .btn-secondary {
    display: inline-block;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--accent);
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    font-weight: 600;
    border: 2px solid var(--accent);
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }
  
  .btn-secondary:hover {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: white;
  }
  
  .trust-signals {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 3rem;
    padding: 2rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin: 2rem 0;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  
  .signal {
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .signal .label {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  
